http://vcctl.cbt.nist.gov/enter.html

        Main Menu for Virtual Cement and Concrete Testing Laboratory
     __________________________________________________________________

  Please select from the following menu:

  0) Access the User's Guide for the VCCTL Frequently Asked Questions

  1) Enter the cement images database system

  2) Create a particle size distribution file

  3) Generate an initial 3-D microstructure

  4) View a 2-D slice from any 3-D microstructure

  5) Generate an animation from any 3-D microstructure

  6) View an animation from any 3-D microstructure

  7) Distribute all phases amongst cement particles

  8) Filter a 3-D microstructure to distribute only two phases amongst cement
  particles

  9) Compute spatial statistics for a 3-D microstructure

  10) Sinter a 3-D microstructure to adjust the hydraulic radius of one phase

  11) Distribute fly ash phases amongst fly ash particles

  12) Input a temperature history (curing) file

  13) Hydrate a 3-D microstructure

  14) Measure phase fractions vs. distance from aggregate

  15) Leach CH/cement from a hydrated microstructure

  16) Evaluate percolation properties of a hydrated/leached microstructure

  17) Plot predicted properties (vs. experimental data)

  18) Predict chloride ion diffusivity of a concrete based on mixture parameters
     __________________________________________________________________
